race.comment: Late bloomer MR CHIPS (7) continued his excellent recent form when the comfortable winner of a Class 1 over this trip at Gunnedah last start. The field dropped away this morning with a couple key late scratchings so he is perfectly placed to take this next step. ZELESTIAL (5) caught the eye over 1400m at Armidale last start, coming from a long way back to get up for third. Suited by the small field. Won over 1600m at the same stage last prep - she should be peaking today. SILENT ACE (6) did his best work late when fresh from a spell last time out over 1318m at this track. Finds a more suitable race today so watch for improvement. AWESOME TYCOON (1) did a great job over seven furlongs here last start when coming off a 37-day let-up. Strips fitter and his record at the mile is solid. The chances end there.
